******
[1]
Date: Fri 30 May 2003
From: Marilda Milagres <mmilagres@cve.saude.sp.gov.br>
Source: Informativo Globo News, Tue 27 May 2003 (trans. by Mod.MPP) [edited]
<http://globonews.globo.com/GloboNews/article/0,6993,A544602-2427,00.html>

Minas Gerais State: Number of Cases Rises to 8
--------------------------------------------------
The Secretary of Health of Minas Gerais confirmed another case of
hantavirus infection in the state on Tue 27 May 2003. This brings to 8 the
number of persons known to be infected. Among the 44 reports, the state
has confirmed 5 deaths [attributable to hantavirus infection]. The regions
most affected are the Mineiro Triangle and the southwest.
Last year [2002] there were 7 deaths reported due to hantavirus infection
in Minas Gerais. The state reference specialist for this disease, Mariana
Gontijo, explained that the increase is due to [spread of infection to] a
new geographic region of the state.
******
[2]
Date: Fri 30 May 2003
From: Marilda Milagres <mmilagres@cve.saude.sp.gov.br>
Source: Agencia Brasil, Thu 29 May 2003 (trans. by Mod.MPP) [edited]
<http://ultimosegundo.ig.com.br/useg/saude/artigo/0,,1217625,00.html>

Santa Catarina State: Another Case of Hantavirus Infection Confirmed
-------------------------------------------------
Another case of hantavirus infection was confirmed in Santa Catarina. A
22-year-old agricultural worker from the city of Treze Tilias, in the
middle-west region of the state, has been hospitalized for 2 weeks in the
Intensive Care Unit of the Joacaba Hospital. Technicians from Health
Surveillance have already inspected the property where he lives, and the
family and surrounding neighbors have been advised of the need for
preventive measures. Since the year 2000 there have been 38 cases of
hantavirus infection with 6 deaths reported in the state.
******
[3]
Date: Fri 30 May 2003
From: Luiz Jacintho da Silva <ljsilva@sucen.gov.br>
Source: ProMED-PORT, Fri 30 May 2003 (trans. by Mod.JW) [edited]

Sao Paulo State: Fatal Case of Hantavirus Infection Confirmed
--------------------------------------------------
The following information has been provided by the Center for
Epidemiological Surveillance of the State Health Secretariat, Sao Paulo.
In Mogi das Cruzes, Sao Paulo, one case of hantavirus infection was
confirmed in a male aged 23 years, who died on Fri 23 May 2003.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The fatal case of hantavirus infection in Sao Paulo was a Chinese man who
was initially thought to have symptoms compatible with SARS. However, it
was established subsequently that he had not been in China for 5 months. -
Mod.JW]
